AFROPOP singer Dapo Aiyegbusi aka Daayuur is set to consolidate on the wild success Nigeria music has made on the global map. The UK based singer says global recognition of Nigerian music has been a major source of motivation for him. He hinted that he feels motivated to sustain and consolidate on the recognition Nigeria music has had on the global map, which will afford him the opportunity to compete for Grammy Award, top music charts, earn mind-boggling endorsements. Known for delivering his lyrics in the English language with an infusion of Pidgin and his native tongue, Yoruba, Daayuur propagates his Nigerian culture as well as love tunes and philosophical narration with the use of his songs. Some of his tracks through which he has endeared himself to music lovers include ‘Gbe e lole,’ ‘She Carry,’ and the most recent,’Obi.’